.Sh CAVEATS
The thermal governor is only started when a PROCHOT override is active
and fans are detected in SMC failsafe mode.
On machines where PROCHOT is not asserted, fans remain under full
SMC automatic control.
.Pp
The
.Va CLWK
key encoding (big-endian vs little-endian) varies by model.
The driver attempts BE first and falls back to LE if the readback
does not match.
.Pp
Disabling the thermal governor via
.Va dev.apple_smc.0.thermal.enabled
sets all override fans to maximum speed as a safety measure.
